      "writtenOn": "2020-08-17T08:46:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since re is the same for all configParser instances, we can initialize it as a global variable.\n\n var splitRe \u003d regexp.MustCompile(`...`)\n\nThen we now have only one field in the struct, so I recommend removing the struct entirely and converting readFiles/readFile to normal functions, passing openedFiles as a function argument, e.g.\n\n func readFile(configFileName string, parentConfig *sshConfig, openedFiles map[string]struct{}) error\n\nSince the parser is actually not very stateful, I recommend implementing it as functions, rather than methods, so that we can ensure statelessness easily.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 50,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 53,
        "endChar": 1
